<subSubSection box="[813,1457,1623,1647]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[813,1457,1623,1647]" box="[813,1457,1623,1647]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">ETYMOLOGY. — The species name refers to the coloration of the face.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="301" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[813,1455,1670,1747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">
DIAGNOSIS. — Aedeagal shaft with one short subapical process on left side, two long spine-shaped processes below it, and two long spine-shaped processes on opposite right side (
<figureCitation box="[1265,1373,1723,1747]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="12.[132,143,1962,1980]" captionTargetBox="[141,1439,229,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@12.[109,1477,201,1901]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIG. 8. — Limentinus nigrifacies n. sp., holotype, ZIN, male genitalia: A, genital block (without aedeagus), lateral view; B, apices of pygofer lobes and anal tube, dorsal view; C, pygofer, ventral view; D, aedeagus, connective, and styles, ventral view; E, aedeagus, connective, and style, lateral view; F, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947035/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Fig. 8D, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="301" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[813,1455,1771,1848]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">
TAXONOMIC RELATIONSHIPS. — In general the male genitalia structure is close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant sensu Nielson (1982)" authorityName="Distant sensu Nielson" authorityYear="1982" box="[963,1387,1797,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Limentinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aldabranus">
<emphasis box="[963,1094,1797,1821]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">L. aldabranus</emphasis>
Distant 
<emphasis box="[1181,1228,1798,1821]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="NIELSON M. W." box="[1236,1387,1797,1821]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 318" refId="ref7093" refString="NIELSON M. W. 1982. - A revision of the subfamily Coelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). IV. Tribe Coelidiini. Pacific Insects Monograph 38: 1 - 318." type="journal article" year="1982">Nielson (1982)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but is well differentiated by its black face and details of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="303" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[813,1455,1906,2028]" box="[813,957,1906,1932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[813,1455,1906,2028]" box="[813,907,1938,1964]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis box="[813,907,1938,1964]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Structure</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[813,1455,1906,2028]" lastBlockId="7.[132,775,1746,1804]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="302" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">General structure as mentioned for the genus. Crown wider than in other species described, as long as wide basally.Second metatarsomere with two spines laterally and two platella between them ventroapically.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947017" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4947017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947017/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" startId="7.[132,143,1641,1659]" targetBox="[146,1449,217,1596]" targetPageId="7">
